<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 20 at 11:28PM CDT  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Jim Hogg and
northeastern Zapata Counties through 1215 AM CDT...
At 1128 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Thompsonville, or 17 miles northeast of Bustamante, moving east at 15
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Randado and Thompsonville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
